<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1721,2033]" box="[199,846,1828,1853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">Integument. Colour yellow. Body surface densely dotted.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1721,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis box="[199,324,1862,1886]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">Prodorsum</emphasis>
with a pair of long lateral carinae. Sensilla long, bacilliform, with fusiform, dilated head covered sparsely with spines. Setae erect (except small exobothridial), rough, interlamellar setae longer than lamellar and rostral setae. Mutual distance between lamellar setae slightly longer than that between rostral setae.
</paragraph>
