<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1381,1877]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,1636,1661]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Comparison.</emphasis>
The new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Mahunka, 1991" authorityName="Mahunka" authorityYear="1991" box="[756,1188,1636,1661]" class="Arachnida" family="Euphthiracaridae" genus="Acrotritia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiculifera">
<emphasis box="[756,993,1637,1661]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Acrotritia spiculifera</emphasis>
(Mahunka, 
<number box="[1123,1180,1636,1660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
but is distinguishable by the presence of tarsi of legs I bi- and legs II-IV triheterodactylous (versus monodactylous) and presence of one pair of genital setae in progenital position (versus 
<number box="[798,812,1708,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" value="3.0">3</number>
pairs of setae). Second similar species 
<taxonomicName authority="Niedbala, 2012" authorityName="Niedbala" authorityYear="2012" class="Arachnida" family="Euphthiracaridae" genus="Acrotritia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraspiculifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Acrotritia paraspiculifera</emphasis>
Niedbała, 
<number box="[446,502,1744,1768]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</taxonomicName>
has two pairs genital setae in progenital position, variable number of claws of tarsi and distance between lamellar setae is distinctly greater than distance between rostral setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="525" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1381,1877]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1817,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Etymology.</emphasis>
The prefix proximus is Latin meaning “the nearest” and refers the similarity between the new species and the species 
<taxonomicName box="[415,652,1853,1877]" class="Arachnida" family="Euphthiracaridae" genus="Acrotritia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiculifera">
<emphasis box="[415,652,1853,1877]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Acrotritia spiculifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[706,994,1853,1877]" class="Arachnida" family="Euphthiracaridae" genus="Acrotritia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraspiculifera">
<emphasis box="[706,994,1853,1877]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Acrotritia paraspiculifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
